
SYSTEM CALLS
------------

This is the system call table.


SYSTEM CALL, FUNCTION  -  DESCRIPTION
-------------------------------------------------------

SYS_MEMORY, SYS_ONE		-  memory alloc/free
SYS_MEMORY, SYS_TWO		-  memory map physical region
SYS_MEMORY, SYS_THREE	-  return size of allocated memory
SYS_MEMORY, SYS_FOUR	-  physical location of alloc'd memory
SYS_MEMORY, SYS_FIVE	-  share/transfer memory
SYS_MEMORY, SYS_SIX		-  accept/reject memory
SYS_MEMORY, SYS_SEVEN	-  release memory





SYS_SEMAPHORE, SYS_ONE	-  create semaphore
SYS_SEMAPHORE, SYS_TWO	-  destroy semaphore
SYS_SEMAPHORE, SYS_THREE-  wait semaphore
SYS_SEMAPHORE, SYS_FOUR	-  signal semaphore
SYS_SEMAPHORE, SYS_FIVE	-  watch semaphore

SYS_SYSTEM, SYS_ONE		-  find pid from name
SYS_SYSTEM, SYS_TWO		-  get name from pid
SYS_SYSTEM, SYS_THREE	-  pid exists

SYS_PROCESS, SYS_ONE	-  get current pid + tid
SYS_PROCESS, SYS_TWO	-  set process state
SYS_PROCESS, SYS_THREE	-  process exit
SYS_PROCESS, SYS_FOUR	-  set the TLS location for the process.
SYS_PROCESS, SYS_FIVE	-  Environment variables.

SYS_THREAD, SYS_ONE	-  spawn thread
SYS_THREAD, SYS_TWO	-  set thread state
SYS_THREAD, SYS_THREE	-  find thread with name
SYS_THREAD, SYS_FOUR	-  go dormant
SYS_THREAD, SYS_FIVE	-  thread exit
SYS_THREAD, SYS_SIX	-  set/get TLS value for thread

SYS_CAP, SYS_ONE	-  remote set
SYS_CAP, SYS_TWO	-  remote get
SYS_CAP, SYS_THREE	-  local set
SYS_CAP, SYS_FOUR	-  local get


SYS_PULSE, SYS_ONE	-  send pulse
SYS_PULSE, SYS_TWO	-  receive pulse
SYS_PULSE, SYS_THREE	-  preview pulse
SYS_PULSE, SYS_FOUR	-  waiting pulse count
SYS_PULSE, SYS_FIVE	-  drop pulse 


SYS_MESSAGE, SYS_ONE	-  send message
SYS_MESSAGE, SYS_TWO	-  receive message
SYS_MESSAGE, SYS_THREE	-  preview pulse
SYS_MESSAGE, SYS_FOUR	-  drop message


SYS_PORT, SYS_ONE	-  create a port
SYS_PORT, SYS_TWO	-  translate a port to a tid
SYS_PORT, SYS_THREE	-  translate a tid to a port
SYS_PORT, SYS_FOUR	-  release a port
SYS_PORT, SYS_FIVE	-  set/get port flags
SYS_PORT, SYS_SIX	-  bulk set/get port flags


SYS_EXEC, SYS_ONE	-  execute memory region

SYS_PCI, SYS_ONE	-  scan pci bus

SYS_TIME, SYS_ONE	-  get rtc time
SYS_TIME, SYS_TWO	-  get system time
SYS_TIME, SYS_THREE	-  delay
SYS_TIME, SYS_FOUR	-  sleep
SYS_TIME, SYS_FIVE	-  wait for pid/tid
SYS_TIME, SYS_SIX	-  yield (release timeslice)

SYS_IRQ, SYS_ONE	-  acquire irq
SYS_IRQ, SYS_TWO	-  release irq
SYS_IRQ, SYS_TWO	-  acknowledge IRQ

SYS_IO, SYS_ONE		-  request/release io port
SYS_IO, SYS_TWO		-  release/request io privileges


SYS_CONSOLE, SYS_ONE	-  get console base
SYS_CONSOLE, SYS_TWO	-  get console size
SYS_CONSOLE, SYS_THREE	-  set active console
SYS_CONSOLE, SYS_FOUR	-  get process' console
SYS_CONSOLE, SYS_FIVE	-  switch process' console

SYS_LFB, SYS_ONE	-  get lfb information
SYS_LFB, SYS_TWO	-  i dunno
SYS_LFB, SYS_THREE	-  request lfb


SYS_INFO, SYS_ONE	-  system information
SYS_INFO, SYS_TWO	-  process information
SYS_INFO, SYS_THREE	-  thread information
SYS_INFO, SYS_FOUR	-  a random number
SYS_INFO, SYS_FIVE	-  spit.. to be removed.
SYS_INFO, SYS_SIX	-  dmesg information

SYS_REBOOT, SYS_ONE	-  reboot


SYS_SHMEM, SYS_ONE		- create shmem
SYS_SHMEM, SYS_TWO		- delete shmem
SYS_SHMEM, SYS_THREE	- grant/revoke shmem
SYS_SHMEM, SYS_FOUR		- request/release shmem
SYS_SHMEM, SYS_FIVE		- find named region
SYS_SHMEM, SYS_SIX		- get region information

